org.sakaiproject.content.impl

Class CheckingOutputStream

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.io.OutputStream
      • javax.servlet.ServletOutputStream
        • org.sakaiproject.content.impl.CheckingOutputStream
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Closeable, Flushable, AutoCloseable

    public class CheckingOutputStream
extends ServletOutputStream
    ServletOutputStream that buffers the first few bytes to try and check if it looks like a HTML document, if it does then it prepends a header and tags on a footer. Once detection of HTML has been done it just passes all calls through the the underlying OutputStream.
    Author:
    buckett
